thread.title_full: Top 25 polls: Michigan State now 6th in AP, 5th in coaches' poll

author: freep.com
title: Top 25 polls: Michigan State now 6th in AP, 5th in coaches' poll
text:
MORE There are eight Power 5 unbeatens left in college football after Utah and Florida State took their first losses of the season Saturday, and Michigan State has moved up one spot in the Associated Press poll to No. 6.
The Spartans (8-0, 4-0 Big Ten) actually fell a spot to No. 5 in the Amway Coaches Poll after Saturday's 52-26 home win over Indiana. Ohio State remained No. 1 in both polls, as has been the case all season.
The latest AP Top 25 | USA TODAY coaches' poll The Spartans will get this week off and Mark Dantonio is going with no practices during the off week for the first time in his career, to help injured players get health and avoid further health issues. MSU returns to action Nov. 7 at Nebraska.
Michigan stayed at No. 15 in the AP poll and No. 17 in the coaches' poll after a bye week. The Wolverines play Minnesota on Saturday.
